Pointer

Pointers are variables that store address of other variables.

//===========================================================
20190805: 
(1) Pointer to Class
A class pointer is a pointer variable that stores address of an object of a class. 
(2) Pointer to Class array
Note: This is to replace the . (dot) with a -> (dash followed by a greater than sign).

